Class LogicSubscriptionSpecSet

java.lang.Object
neupaths.api.SubscriptionSpecSet
neupaths.api.LogicSubscriptionSpecSet
All Implemented Interfaces:
Iterable<SubscriptionSpec>
public final class LogicSubscriptionSpecSet extends SubscriptionSpecSet
Maintains a collection of LogicSubscriptionSpec objects. This type is passed to Activator constructors.

    • LogicSubscriptionSpecSet

      public LogicSubscriptionSpecSet(String cellName, String transmitterName, String receptorName, String domain, TransactionFilter filterTransactions)
      Creates a subscription set with a single logic subscription element.
      Parameters:
      cellName - The name of the cell or injector that created the stimulus. This value may contain a regular expression.
      transmitterName - The name of the transmitter that sent the stimulus. This value may contain a regular expression.
      receptorName - The name of the receptor to receive the stimulus. This value may not contain a regular expression.
      domain - The domain in which the stimulus will be processed.
      filterTransactions - For stimuli that are service responses, filters redundant responses.
